<collectingRegion box="[359,458,1339,1361]" country="Italy" name="Sardegna" pageId="7" pageNumber="422">Sardinien</collectingRegion>
(Dorgali, Mte. Aqueri&quot; (
<bibRefCitation author="BERNHAUER M" box="[735,928,1339,1361]" pageId="7" pageNumber="422" pagination="123 - 129" refId="ref7714" refString="BERNHAUER M. (1935): Neuheiten der palaarktischen Staphylinidenfauna. II. Neue Leptusa - Arten. - Koleopterologische Rundschau 21 (3 / 4): 123 - 129." type="journal article" year="1935">BERNHAUER 1935</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="PACE R" box="[951,1085,1339,1361]" pageId="7" pageNumber="422" pagination="1978 - 1979" refId="ref7997" refString="PACE R. (1979): Leptusa KR. nuove o poco note del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova (Coleoptera Staphylinidae). - Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale &quot; Giacomo Doria &quot; 82 [1978 - 1979]: 295 - 322." type="journal article" year="1979">PACE (1979)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1935" box="[320,418,1368,1390]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="422" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sardoa">
<emphasis box="[320,418,1368,1390]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="422">L. sardoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1935" box="[479,642,1368,1390]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="422" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hummleriana">
<emphasis box="[479,642,1368,1390]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="422">L. hummleriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and in referring to the type specimen from the Bernhauer collection as &quot;il tipo&quot; unintentionally designated a 
<typeStatus box="[840,936,1397,1419]" pageId="7" pageNumber="422">lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[178,1086,1435,1603]" pageId="7" pageNumber="422">
In the collections of the NHMW, eleven specimens labelled as cotypes of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1935" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="422" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hummleriana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="422">L. hummleriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and seven labelled as cotypes of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1935" box="[661,759,1464,1486]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="422" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sardoa">
<emphasis box="[661,759,1464,1486]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="422">L. sardoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were found. However, some of them had evidently been mislabelled by Scheerpeltz. Four of the specimens labelled as cotypes of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1935" box="[302,470,1522,1544]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="422" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hummleriana">
<emphasis box="[302,470,1522,1544]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="422">L. hummleriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are from Dorgali and consequently 
<typeStatus box="[872,1018,1522,1544]" pageId="7" pageNumber="422">paralectotypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1935" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="422" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sardoa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="422">L. sardoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and two of the specimens labelled as cotypes of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1935" box="[771,870,1552,1574]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="422" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sardoa">
<emphasis box="[771,870,1552,1574]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="422">L. sardoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are from Aritzo and thus represent 
<typeStatus box="[326,472,1581,1603]" pageId="7" pageNumber="422">paralectotypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1935" box="[506,667,1581,1603]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="422" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hummleriana">
<emphasis box="[506,667,1581,1603]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="422">L. hummleriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[178,1085,218,358]" pageId="8" pageNumber="423">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1935" box="[178,401,218,240]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="423" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hummleriana">
<emphasis box="[178,401,218,240]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="423">Leptusa hummleriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is remarkably widespread in 
<collectingRegion box="[709,793,218,240]" country="Italy" name="Sardegna" pageId="8" pageNumber="423">Sardinia</collectingRegion>
and has been reported from various localities both in the north and in the south of the island. For additional records see 
<bibRefCitation author="PACE R" box="[218,350,277,299]" pageId="8" pageNumber="423" pagination="1 - 307" refId="ref8085" refString="PACE R. (1989): Monografia del genere Leptusa KRAATZ (Coleoptera Staphylinidae). - Memorie del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Verona (II a Serie), Sezione Scienze della Vita (A: Biologica) 8: 1 - 307." type="journal article" year="1989">PACE (1989)</bibRefCitation>
. The shape of the aedeagus varies slightly between populations, but the observed differences (
<figureCitation box="[417,536,306,328]" captionStart="Figs 11-20" captionStartId="9.[178,218,1488,1508]" captionTargetBox="[179,1066,213,1475]" captionTargetId="figure-1@9.[178,1070,212,1475]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 11-20: Leptusa meybohmi nov.sp. (11-16) and L. hummleriana BERNHAUER (17-20; 17: paralectotype of L. hummleriana; 18: paralectotype of L. sardoa from Dorgali; 19: male from Catena del Márghine; 20: male from Monte Arci): (11) habitus; (12) forebody; (13) male tergite VIII; (14) male sternite VIII; (15-20) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 11: 1.0 mm; 12: 0.5 mm; 13-14: 0.2 mm; 15-20: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4526296" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4526296/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="423">Figs 17-20</figureCitation>
) are interpreted as intra- rather than interspecific variation.
</paragraph>
